ce:section.ce:para:
Under the experimental conditions, CDCa, CDN, GO, GONR, C60, AuNP, and AgNP all exhibit catalysis of the reduction between HAuCl4 and GLC to produce AuNPs. With the increase of the catalyst concentration (Cc), the produced nanogold increased due to the catalytic ability increasing. With VBB as the probe, the SERS signal enhanced linearly. Here, we used the slope of linear curve between I1615 cm−1
                         and Cc to evaluate the catalysis, in which the slope is big and the catalysis is strong, due to the evaluating procedure being of simple and rapid. Among them, the catalytic activity of CDCa4 is the strongest, followed by C60 and GONR. The catalytic activities of CDN, GO, AuNP and AgNP were relatively weakest. Comparing to CDCa1-CDCa7 (Table 1
                        ), we known that the catalysis of CDCa4 is stronger than the CDCa1, this is owing to doped-metal Ca enhancing the surface electrons. More surface electrons accelerate the redox-electron transfer, and produced more AuNPs (Fig. 7
                        ). Addition of Apt to the system, Apt adsorb on nanocatalyst surface by hydrophobic forces, it can block the contact between nanocatalyst catalyst and the reactants of HAuCl4 and GLC to inhibit the catalytic activity, the SERS at I1615 cm−1
                         also shows a linear relationship with Apt concentration. The slope of Apt-CDCa4 system is biggest, and the inhibition is strongest.

To the Apt-TB-HAuCl4-GLC-CDCa4-VBB SERS system, the SERS ΔI responds linearly with the TB concentration (CTB) in the range (LR) of 0.0058–0.115 nmol/L, with a linear regression equation of ΔI = 62837CTB – 386.6 and a detection limit (DL) of 0.0023 nmol/L. From Table 1, we can see that the catalytic activity of CDCa4 is the strongest due to the doped-Ca levels being of largest surface electrons with enhancing the redox electron-transfer of HAuCl4-GLC reaction. In the SERS detection, the CDCa1-7 was used as catalyst to amplify SERS analytical signal, if the catalysis of CDCa is stronger the thrombin detection is more sensitive. Thus, the CDCa4 SERS detection system is the most sensitive (Table 3
                        ), and was chosen for use. The SERS quantitative analytical method was compared to the reported method for determination of TB (Table 4
                        ) [33–40], it has a wide linear range, high sensitivity and selectivity, simplicity and rapidity, label-free, and is one of best sensitive method for thrombin.
